what is the main cause of climate change?

The main driver of climate change is human activities, primarily due to the burning of fossil fuels like coal, oil, and natural gas. This process releases greenhouse gases, mainly carbon dioxide (CO2) and methane, into the atmosphere, leading to long-term shifts in global temperatures and weather patterns.
